The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Saturday, December 07, 2002  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	Ragini Vimal, numero uno in the state, lifted the womens singles crown at the Saturday Club floodlit tournament beating Reedhina Parekh 6-4, 6-2 in Fridays final. This was her fourth title of the meet. 				 																																																	In mens singles, Harshit Sharma prevented an all-Sewa final by scalping elder brother Vinod 6-0, 2-6, 6-3. In Fridays other semi-final, Manoj Sewa fought off Abhishek Jagnani 6-2, 2-6, 7-5. The mens final comes off Saturday evening.				 																																																	Beginning Sunday, coach Sayandeb Chakraborty will supervise four-hour daily sessions where all seven players  Vinod Sewa, Harshit Sharma, Abhishek Jagnani, Rupesh Roy, Ragini Vimal, Reedhina Parekh and Tania Ahuja  will work out. 				 																																																	Enrico Piperno may help out too. The squad will leave for Hyderabad on Thursday.				 																																																	This was announced at a press conference Friday evening.				 																																																	The teams will be divided into two groups of three each. The top two will qualify for the final while the other four will compete for the Losers Plate.				 																																																	In Fridays semis, Damani saw off Mahfooz Alam 3-2 while Hussain edged past Saurav Kothari 3-2.				 																																																	TENNIS: Saturday Club floodlit meet: Mens Open singles final from 5.30 pm.				 																																																	SNOOKER: N.K. Sood Memorial handicap meet: Final at YMCA 				 																																																	College branch from 5 pm.
